wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Hancock (23 August 1856 – 8 February 1916) was an Australian politician who represented the South Australian House of Assembly seat of Newcastle from 1890 to 1893.

response: Hancock was a left-arm medium pace bowler and took 94 first-class wickets at an average of 29.73 and a best performance of 5 for 61. He was a left-hand batsman and played 77 innings in 48 first-class matches with an average of 7.91 and a top score of 43 not out.Joseph Hancock at Cricket Archive
